HEADWORD: Zygenid
<hw>Zyg"e*nid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gr. <?/,
probably the hammer-headed shark.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one
of numerous species of moths of the family <fam>Zygaenidae</fam>, most
of which are bright colored. The wood nymph and the vine forester are
examples. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

